    <question>
        <prompt>Herbert Hoover's concept of "American Individualism" emphasized:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Government intervention in the economy</option>
            <option letter="b">Self-reliance and voluntary cooperation</option>
            <option letter="c">Socialist economic principles</option>
            <option letter="d">Direct federal aid to the poor</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Hoover's "American Individualism" philosophy stressed the importance of self-reliance, voluntary cooperation, and limited government intervention. He believed that American progress depended on individual initiative and private sector solutions rather than direct government assistance. This ideology significantly influenced his response to the Great Depression, leading him to resist direct federal aid to individuals.</explanation>
    </question>
